# Component Architecture

## Design Goal

Build **comprehensive, reusable components** that work across multiple screens — not one-off UI tied to a single feature.

## Component Checklist

Every shared component must have:

- [ ] Explicit props interface (extend native props when wrapping primitives)
- [ ] Sensible defaults so simple usage is one line
- [ ] Variants via props (e.g. `type`, `size`, `variant`) — not copy-pasted components
- [ ] Theme integration via `useTheme()` or theme tokens
- [ ] All UI states: default, disabled, loading, error (when applicable)
- [ ] Accessibility: `accessibilityRole`, `accessibilityLabel`, hit slop for touch targets
- [ ] Platform-safe behavior (web vs native differences)

## Structure

```tsx
// 1. Imports
// 2. Types / props interface (exported)
// 3. Component (named export, functional)
// 4. Styles (StyleSheet.create at bottom)
```

## Composition Over Duplication

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — duplicate button styles in every screen
// ✅ GOOD — single Button component with variant prop
<Button variant="primary" onPress={handleSubmit} loading={isPending}>
  Save
</Button>
```

## Folder Layout

```
src/components/
  ui/           # Primitive building blocks (Button, Input, Card)
  themed-*.tsx  # Theme-aware wrappers
  feature/      # Feature-specific composites (only if reused within feature)
```

- `ui/` = generic, app-wide primitives
- Feature-specific components stay near their feature unless reused elsewhere

## Props API Rules

- Extend underlying primitive props (`TextProps`, `ViewProps`, `PressableProps`) with `Omit` when overriding.
- Use discriminated unions for mutually exclusive prop groups.
- Avoid boolean prop explosion — group related options into a `variant` or `size` enum.
- Forward `ref` when wrapping interactive or measurable elements.

## AppText

Use `variant`, `mode`, and `weight` from `@/components/ui/app-text` — not inline `fontSize`, `lineHeight`, `letterSpacing`, or `fontFamily`. See `typography.mdc` for full rules.

## Do Not

- Put data fetching, navigation, or global store logic inside primitive UI components.
- Export default and named for the same component.
- Create "God components" that handle layout + data + actions + styling in one file.
